# Cellule.ai maintainers — release signing keys
#
# This file lists the Ed25519 public keys authorized to sign official
# releases (Python wheel + Docker image). It is a SUPPLY-CHAIN file,
# not a governance file — a key in MAINTAINERS grants zero privilege
# on the network itself. Pool nodes function normally without it.
#
# Format (one maintainer per non-comment line):
#   <nickname> <pubkey_hex_64> <added_date_YYYY-MM-DD> [<contact>]
#
# Rules:
#   - Bootstrap: K=1 (David only). Transitional, not decentralized.
#   - :stable channel requires K >= 2 signatures before publication.
#   - Key rotation requires quorum signature from current maintainers.
#   - Pool verification is WARNING-only (never rejects a release) so
#     a signing-key loss never takes a worker offline. Operators who
#     want strict verification can set IAMINE_STRICT_SIGNING=1.
#
# See docs/GOVERNANCE.md for the full rationale.

